720.question: How much is proposed model better than baselines in performed experiments?
720.response:
To answer the question about how much the proposed model is better than the baselines in the performed experiments, I will analyze the chart in Image 3, which seems to display the results of experiments comparing different models.

Based on the table in Image 3, we can see three models listed as E2ECM, CDM, and GDP both with and without reinforcement learning (RL). There are different metrics used to assess these models, such as BLEU score, BPRA (Binary Precision-Recall AUC), and APRA (Average Precision-Recall AUC), as well as time taken for full evaluation (T_time
720.answer:
most of the models have similar performance on BPRA: DSTC2 (+0.0015), Maluuba (+0.0729)
GDP achieves the best performance in APRA: DSTC2 (+0.2893), Maluuba (+0.2896)
GDP significantly outperforms the baselines on BLEU: DSTC2 (+0.0791), Maluuba (+0.0492)
